{"article_id":"NE14pvPn4EMAUxJL","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" While there may be disagreement in Congress over whether or not to raise taxes on folks","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"making over $ 250,000 a year ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"nobody","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"- not Republicans , not Democrats -","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"want taxes to go up for folks","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"making under $ 250,000 a year , \"","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"he said .","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"\" So let ' s not wait . \"","depth":3},{"id":8,"text":"The president ' s comments came","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"shortly after Speaker John A. Boehner ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"who had been striking a conciliatory tone since Republican election losses in the Senate and the House ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"told reporters","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"that Republicans had won a mandate of their own","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"by retaining control of the House","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"and that he supported continuing rates","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"enacted in the Bush-era tax cuts for all income levels .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"\" Raising tax rates will slow down our ability","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"to create the jobs","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"that everyone says","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"they want , \"","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"said Mr. Boehner ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"who said","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"he favored generating any new federal revenue","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"to offset the deficit","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"by closing tax loopholes","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"and limiting deductions .","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"\" It ' s clear that there are a lot of special interest loopholes in the tax code , both corporate and personal , \"","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"\" It ' s also clear that there are all kinds of deductions ,","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"some of which make sense ;","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"others don ' t .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"And","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"by lowering rates","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"and cleaning up the tax code ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"we know","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"we ' re going to get more economic growth . \"","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"The president and Mr. Boehner were careful with their language","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"and left room for compromise","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"despite their fundamental differences","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"about shifting more of the tax burden to high-income Americans .","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"Mr. Boehner would not be very specific on what his goal might be","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"for raising new federal tax dollars .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"\" I don ' t want to box myself in , \"","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"\" I don ' t want to box anybody else in .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"I think","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"it ' s important for us to come to an agreement with the president .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"But this is his opportunity","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"to lead . \"","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"The speaker ,","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"who has struggled with his more conservative rank and file in the past ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"he was confident","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"that he could pass a deal","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"if one was reached with the White House .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"\" When the president and I have been able to come to an agreement ,","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"there has been no problem","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"getting it passed here in the House , \"","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"Newsletter Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"Continue reading the main story","depth":5},{"id":61,"text":"Please verify","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"you 're not a robot","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"by clicking the box .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"Invalid email address .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"Please re-enter .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"You must select a newsletter","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"to subscribe to .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"Sign Up","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"You will receive emails","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"containing news content , updates and promotions from The New York Times .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"You may opt-out at any time .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"You agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for The New York Times 's products and services .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"Thank you for subscribing .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"An error has occurred .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"Please try again later .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"View all New York Times newsletters .","depth":3},{"id":77,"text":"House Republican leadership aides found some positive signals in Mr. Obama ' s combative tone .","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"They noted","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"that he never specified","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"he wants tax rates to rise ,","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"only that he wants additional revenues","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"generated by taxes on the rich .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"That would give both sides the latitude","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"to devise a restructured tax code","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"that eliminates or limits tax deductions and credits for the rich","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"- or that follows Mitt Romney ' s proposal","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"to cap deductions at a set limit for rich households ,","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"though many analysts say","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"that approach alone can not raise the revenue","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"Democrats want .","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Any agreement","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"to avert a fiscal crisis in January ,","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"when hundreds of billions of dollars in automatic tax increases and spending cuts kick in ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"now revolves around the definition of tax increases .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"Mr. Boehner is holding the line against any increase in tax rates , even for the richest Americans ,","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"who currently are in the 35 percent tax bracket .","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"But he is leaving open the possibility of a tax overhaul","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"that raises more revenue than the existing code .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"Representative Steny H. Hoyer of Maryland , the No . 2 Democrat , echoed the view at the White House","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"that Americans want to see taxes on the wealthy go up .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"In a statement","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"after Mr. Obama spoke ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"Mr. Hoyer said","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"that \" on Tuesday , the American people made it clear","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"that they support a balanced approach","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"to bring down deficits","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"and set our nation back on a sound fiscal path -","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"one","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"that does not ask working families and those","depth":17},{"id":110,"text":"struggling to get by","depth":17},{"id":111,"text":"to bear the burden of deficit reduction ,","depth":16},{"id":112,"text":"but instead asks the wealthiest Americans to pay their fair share . \"","depth":15},{"id":113,"text":"While Mr. Obama was careful not to demand","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"that tax rates rise ,","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"Jay Carney , the White House press secretary , said just an hour later","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"that the president would veto any legislation","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"extending the expiring tax cuts for families","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"making $ 250,000 or more .","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"For all the talk of compromise , neither side offered any suggestion","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"of where it might back down .","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"While both sides agree on the need","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"to avoid triggering the automatic tax increases and spending cuts","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"that occur","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"if there is no deal","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"- and there is deep concern","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"that failure could harm the economy -","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"the shape of a final compromise remains unclear .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"New reports this week by the Congressional Budget Office found","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"that the automatic tax increases and spending cuts would cut the deficit by $ 503 billion through next September .","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"But the reports said","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"that the austerity could cause the economy to shrink by 0.5 percent next year ,","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"and would lead to the loss of millions of jobs .","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"The Congressional leaders will be heading to the White House on Friday ,","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"administration officials said ,","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"just before Mr. Obama leaves for Cambodia , Myanmar and Thailand ,","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"where he will attend economic meetings with world leaders .","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"He is certain to come under pressure there","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"to reach a deal with Republicans","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"since the American economy is doing better than most other global economies ,","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"and a slowdown in the United States is widely viewed as potentially catastrophic to the global economy .","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"\" It ' s time","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"to get back to work , \"","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"the president said at the White House .","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"\" And there is plenty of work to do . \"","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":289,"left":203,"right":288,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":152,"right":202,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":151,"right":7,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":151,"left":150,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":146,"right":149,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":146,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":147,"right":148,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":147,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":179,"right":201,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":159,"right":178,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":8,"right":158,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":154,"right":157,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":154,"left":153,"right":11,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":155,"right":156,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":155,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":168,"right":177,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":162,"right":167,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":162,"left":16,"right":161,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":17,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":167,"left":20,"right":166,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":21,"right":165,"r